The paper deals with the study of a new class of graphs called Paired Threshold (PT) graphs, which are used to model economic and social interactions. The paper discusses the characterization, decomposition, forbidden induced subgraphs, vertex weight assignments, and recognition of PT graphs. These topics are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM), social networks (cs.SI), graph theory (cs.GT), and network economics (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper analyzes the intersection number, diameter, and clustering coefficient of PT graphs, which are topics related to social dynamics (cs.SD). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.GT, and cs.NE.
